<span id="freeTextContainer15001423809964741833">I kind of hated this book because of how unhealthy Marisol and Olivia&apos;s relationship is. Even though the age difference turns out not to be that large, I still felt creeped out by the actual age difference and how Olivia takes advantage of Marisol. While I sympathized with Marisol&apos;s struggles throughout the course of the relationship, I also had a hard time believing she could be so naive that she doesn&apos;t question any of Olivia&apos;s controlling and honestly borderline (if not outright) abusive beha</span>
  <span id="freeText15001423809964741833" style="display:none">I kind of hated this book because of how unhealthy Marisol and Olivia's relationship is. Even though the age difference turns out not to be that large, I still felt creeped out by the actual age difference and how Olivia takes advantage of Marisol. While I sympathized with Marisol's struggles throughout the course of the relationship, I also had a hard time believing she could be so naive that she doesn't question any of Olivia's controlling and honestly borderline (if not outright) abusive behavior. It was hard watching her endure it all and I was glad when it was over. I was also glad that she doesn't get together with Lee at the end since she doesn't deserve her, at least not right away. The only reason I gave this book two stars instead of one is because I liked most of the other characters and enjoyed Marisol's writing and writing process.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15001423809964741833" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

