    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_122807598" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/122807598" />
    <a title="Charlisa-isb" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4321569-charlisa-isb"><img alt="Charlisa-isb" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/122807598?book_show_action=true">Sep 21, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Charlisa-isb" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Charlisa-isb" href="/user/show/4321569-charlisa-isb">Charlisa-isb</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781416979142" href="/book/show/7003447-love-lies">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer122807598&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer122807598" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15464182885373814354">Love and Lies by Ellen Wittlinger is about a lesbian girl name Marisol Guzman who is taking a year off college at her gay best friend, Birdie’s house, to do two things: find romance and write a novel. In the beginning, this is exactly what she gets by signing up for a writing course. Marisol then finds her old friend, John Galardi (Gio), from the first novel Hard Love, who joins the course. Afterwards, Marisol falls in love with her English Teacher, Olivia Frost, and later on starts a relationsh</span>
  <span id="freeText15464182885373814354" style="display:none">Love and Lies by Ellen Wittlinger is about a lesbian girl name Marisol Guzman who is taking a year off college at her gay best friend, Birdie’s house, to do two things: find romance and write a novel. In the beginning, this is exactly what she gets by signing up for a writing course. Marisol then finds her old friend, John Galardi (Gio), from the first novel Hard Love, who joins the course. Afterwards, Marisol falls in love with her English Teacher, Olivia Frost, and later on starts a relationship with her. However conflict arises when her English instructor ends up lying about her love to Marisol. As the story continues, she struggles to see the truth in Olivia and tries to write a novel without having her relationship pull her down with the help of John and other friends along the way. <br />After reading Love and Lies by Ellen Wittlinger, I felt that it was a well written novel. Despite having the same gender fall in love, i thought it was quiet interesting. I was very excited about her finding romance, but disappointed that it was not what she expected. I loved how she had her friends to help her throughout her struggle with Olivia and how John played the role in helping her realize what was the conflict because of what happened in the previous novel . Overall, it was very fascinating novel. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="15464182885373814354" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

